"Moreover, the relative importance of the measures designed to control parasitic infections differs from that of measures to control other communicable diseases (environmental hygiene, in particular). # Control Programs\nThe control of intestinal parasites can be limited to the control of the diseases caused by the parasites, or it can be expanded to include control of parasitic infection. The first case calls for an individual approach; in the second, the orientation is communal and focuses on environmental hygiene, the water supply, health education, essential drugs, food and nutrition, epidemiology, etc."